    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the period in Upper Egypt from about 6000 to 4000 BCE associated with finds excavated at Badari. Works of art include anthropomorphic figurines, slate palettes, and black-topped pottery or pottery decorated with a ripple-burnished surface.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al período en el Alto Egipto desde aproximadamente el 6000 al 4000 a.C., asociado con hallazgos excavados en Badari. Las obras de arte incluyen estatuillas antropomórficas, paletas de pizarra y cerámica con ribete negro o cerámica decorada con una superficie "ripple-burnished".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de periode in Boven-Egypte van circa 6000 tot 4000 v. Chr. die wordt geassocieerd met opgravingen bij Badari. De kunstwerken omvatten onder meer antropomorfe figuren, leistenen paletten en aardewerk met een zwarte top of aardewerk met een ripple-burnished oppervlak.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指自西元前6000年至西元前4000年間在上埃及發展的時代，
與巴達里（Badari）一地的考古發現有關。藝術品包括擬人化的小型塑像、化妝調色板與頂部著以黑色的陶器或表面以波紋加以裝飾的拋光陶器。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
